1
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:35,840
Director Lin, I mean...

2
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:37,200
You're terrifying.

3
00:01:38,480 --> 00:01:40,000
What were those two saying just now?

4
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,879
I honestly didn't understand a word.

5
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:43,200
That whole scene

6
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:44,000
reminded me of

7
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:45,079
my homeroom teacher

8
00:01:45,079 --> 00:01:46,200
back in middle school.

9
00:01:46,599 --> 00:01:48,959
They were examining her and quizzing her.

10
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:50,200
Scary.

11
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:52,000
Zhang Diao'e,

12
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:53,879
your condition is complicated.

13
00:01:53,959 --> 00:01:55,120
You need to be admitted for tests

14
00:01:55,239 --> 00:01:55,879
before we can consider

15
00:01:55,879 --> 00:01:56,840
a surgical plan.

16
00:01:58,079 --> 00:01:59,040
Surgery?

17
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:02,400
Can I still get pregnant this year?

18
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:03,480
Get pregnant?

19
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:07,560
Didn't one of you just say

20
00:02:07,599 --> 00:02:10,000
something about it being congenital?

21
00:02:10,319 --> 00:02:11,960
I'm already this old.

22
00:02:12,199 --> 00:02:13,479
I've had two daughters

23
00:02:13,479 --> 00:02:14,719
without any problems.

24
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:16,199
Having another son

25
00:02:16,599 --> 00:02:17,840
shouldn't be a big deal, right?

26
00:02:18,159 --> 00:02:19,319
You were lucky before.

27
00:02:20,439 --> 00:02:21,199
First, we need to deal with

28
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:22,199
your illness.

29
00:02:22,439 --> 00:02:23,400
Then we can consider everything else.

30
00:02:23,639 --> 00:02:24,039
Okay?

31
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,159
Hey, everyone.

32
00:02:28,439 --> 00:02:30,280
Xiao'e is at a major hospital now.

33
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:32,240
The doctors say she has

34
00:02:32,319 --> 00:02:34,240
an extremely rare disease,

35
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:35,000
called...

36
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:36,599
a PPA... something fistula.

37
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:38,919
Xiao'e

38
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:39,680
is now going

39
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:41,560
to see another doctor.

40
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:43,639
She's feeling

41
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:45,400
very unsettled,

42
00:02:46,599 --> 00:02:48,560
like water sloshing

43
00:02:48,919 --> 00:02:50,400
around in a bucket.

44
00:02:51,319 --> 00:02:52,159
We don't even know

45
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:13,159
if she's still dizzy.

46
00:03:13,159 --> 00:03:14,360
Very dizzy. Very dizzy.

47
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:16,120
Let me catch my breath.

48
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:18,520
It hurts here. Here.

49
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:19,879
Please bear with it.

50
00:03:19,879 --> 00:03:20,520
I'll disinfect the wound.

51
00:03:20,759 --> 00:03:21,159
Okay.

52
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:22,360
It may have been

53
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:23,360
a transient faint from hypoxia.

54
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:24,199
We also can't rule out

55
00:03:24,199 --> 00:03:25,360
the risk of a cerebral infarction.

56
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:26,759
And she hit her head.

57
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:28,280
Let's arrange

58
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:29,479
a brain MRI.

59
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:32,120
It's already been ordered.

60
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:34,319
Come outside with me.

61
00:03:39,879 --> 00:03:40,960
Both sides hurt.

62
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:41,919
Easy.

63
00:03:42,759 --> 00:03:43,400
Why did you dodge?

64
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:47,360
She fell right in front of you.

65
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:48,560
Why didn't you catch her?

66
00:03:53,759 --> 00:03:54,719
She's your patient.

67
00:03:55,319 --> 00:03:56,879
You know how dangerous her condition is.

68
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,360
She was lucky this time.

69
00:03:58,879 --> 00:03:59,759
Nothing serious happened.

70
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,159
But what if something had?

71
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:02,159
Would you take responsibility?

72
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:03,800
She fell on her own.

73
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:04,960
Why should I be responsible?

74
00:04:05,199 --> 00:04:06,400
This is a hospital. You're a doctor.

75
00:04:06,680 --> 00:04:07,400
Yes, I'm a doctor.

76
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:08,360
Just a doctor.

77
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,560
I'm not special forces.

78
00:04:09,879 --> 00:04:10,479
What were you afraid of?

79
00:04:11,919 --> 00:04:12,919
Any ordinary person

80
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:13,840
who saw someone falling

81
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:14,719
would try to help.

82
00:04:15,039 --> 00:04:15,680
But you?

83
00:04:16,079 --> 00:04:16,800
Not only did you not help,

84
00:04:17,399 --> 00:04:18,040
you dodged.

85
00:04:19,240 --> 00:04:20,279
In that moment,

86
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:21,399
maybe she didn't react in time.

87
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:22,279
She reacted.

88
00:04:22,759 --> 00:04:23,560
She dodged very quickly.

89
00:04:24,879 --> 00:04:25,480
Am I not allowed to?

90
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:27,839
Can't I protect myself?

91
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,079
Do I have to risk my own life?

92
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:31,920
I'm only human.

93
00:04:32,319 --> 00:04:33,439
I only have one life.

94
00:04:33,839 --> 00:04:34,279
Fine.

95
00:04:37,079 --> 00:04:38,240
don't wear that uniform

96
00:04:41,879 --> 00:04:43,040
Don't let me see you again.

97
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:55,040
Director Lin is just like that.

98
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:57,199
In his eyes,

99
00:04:57,879 --> 00:04:59,160
the patient's safety comes first.

100
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,079
That's why he spoke so harshly.

101
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:06,319
In that situation,

102
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:08,560
you chose to dodge.

103
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:11,480
I can't say you were wrong.

104
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:17,480
For now, take good care of the patient.

105
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:18,639
I'll speak with

106
00:05:18,639 --> 00:05:19,600
Director Lin again.

107
00:05:38,199 --> 00:05:40,160
Look at this huge hole.

108
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:42,120
These shoes are brand-new.

109
00:05:42,199 --> 00:05:43,560
I've only worn them a few days.

110
00:05:44,279 --> 00:05:46,600
What a shame.

111
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,399
Look, two holes.

112
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:53,120
It still hurts a little.

113
00:05:53,319 --> 00:05:55,040
Be careful when you go back.

114
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:19,800
Tell your doctor

115
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:21,519
if anything changes. Thank you.

116
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:24,879
The wheelchair is here.

117
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,279
Pretty doctor, you're here.

118
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:27,360
I'll take you back to the ward.

119
00:06:28,759 --> 00:06:29,839
We've dressed the wound here.

120
00:06:30,079 --> 00:06:31,199
Don't get it wet.

121
00:06:31,519 --> 00:06:31,879
Understood.

122
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:32,279
All right.

123
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:33,319
Do I have to sit in this?

124
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:35,680
My leg wasn't injured.

125
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:37,040
I can walk by myself.

126
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:37,439
Sit.

127
00:06:40,319 --> 00:06:42,000
I heard what they said about you.

128
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:42,800
I'm sorry.

129
00:06:42,879 --> 00:06:44,000
I caused you trouble.

130
00:06:44,079 --> 00:06:45,000
This has nothing to do with you.

131
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:46,959
Actually, you were right to dodge.

132
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:47,920
I'm a big woman.

133
00:06:47,959 --> 00:06:49,199
If I'd fallen on you

134
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,160
and hurt you,

135
00:06:50,399 --> 00:06:51,680
your parents would be heartbroken.

136
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:54,040
You're only a few years older

137
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:55,040
than my eldest daughter.

138
00:06:55,319 --> 00:06:56,600
Raising such an

139
00:06:56,639 --> 00:06:57,519
outstanding daughter

140
00:06:57,519 --> 00:06:58,399
isn't easy.

141
00:06:58,720 --> 00:06:59,240
You couldn't have

142
00:06:59,279 --> 00:07:00,240
a daughter as old as me.

143
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:01,199
Stop talking. Get some rest.

144
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:02,560
She's kind of funny.

145
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:04,279
Wait.

146
00:07:05,319 --> 00:07:06,160
I still have a bag.

147
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:07,439
I forgot it.

148
00:07:07,839 --> 00:07:08,560
Don't run.

149
00:07:15,759 --> 00:07:16,560
It sounds pretty good.

150
00:07:16,839 --> 00:07:17,720
You're recovering well.

151
00:07:18,759 --> 00:07:19,079
Come on.

152
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:20,839
Let me check the incision.

153
00:07:25,519 --> 00:07:26,600
It's healing well too.

154
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:27,680
No sign of infection.

155
00:07:28,519 --> 00:07:28,839
Dadong,

156
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,160
if you feel

157
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:31,519
pain at the incision or anywhere else,

158
00:07:31,519 --> 00:07:32,720
tell us immediately.

159
00:07:32,839 --> 00:07:33,639
Don't try to endure it.

160
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:35,680
If you need to cough,

161
00:07:35,759 --> 00:07:37,160
hold your chest with your hand

162
00:07:37,399 --> 00:07:38,560
or a pillow.

163
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:39,639
It protects the wound

164
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:40,959
and helps you clear phlegm.

165
00:07:40,959 --> 00:07:42,279
As for food,

166
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,720
eat light, soft meals.

167
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:44,839
And since you've been

168
00:07:44,879 --> 00:07:45,720
in bed for so long,

169
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:47,639
remember to move your feet and legs.

170
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:48,680
Keep them moving.

171
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:50,720
It helps prevent venous thrombosis.

172
00:07:50,959 --> 00:07:51,759
Your heart rate

173
00:07:51,839 --> 00:07:53,160
may be a little fast lately.

174
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:54,279
That's normal.

175
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:55,199
Your heart

176
00:07:55,199 --> 00:07:56,600
needs time to adjust.

177
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:58,199
But overall,

178
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:00,000
you're doing very well.

179
00:08:01,399 --> 00:08:02,560
Dr. Du

180
00:08:02,959 --> 00:08:03,600
encourages me

181
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:05,360
like I'm a three-year-old.

182
00:08:05,639 --> 00:08:06,920
Dr. Du is very serious.

183
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:08,680
He put all your clinical data

184
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:09,759
into a chart

185
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,519
and even did a full analysis.

186
00:08:12,279 --> 00:08:13,000
He put a lot of effort into it.

187
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:13,959
Thank you.

188
00:08:14,959 --> 00:08:15,959
It's my job.

189
00:08:19,199 --> 00:08:20,959
Dr. Fang is amazing.

190
00:08:21,319 --> 00:08:23,079
She's gentle and attentive,

191
00:08:23,319 --> 00:08:24,439
and she even notices my strengths.

192
00:08:24,959 --> 00:08:25,279
Seriously.

193
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:26,439
Working with her versus Director Lin

194
00:08:26,480 --> 00:08:27,199
is like heaven

195
00:08:27,279 --> 00:08:28,199
and hell.

196
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,720
Buddy, do you have a crush?

197
00:08:29,959 --> 00:08:30,920
Isn't that a little exaggerated?

198
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:31,879
No, seriously.

199
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,639
Dr. Fang is great.

200
00:08:33,639 --> 00:08:34,360
You have no idea.

201
00:08:35,279 --> 00:08:36,279
Watch yourself.

202
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:37,279
Just because Director Lin isn't here,

203
00:08:37,279 --> 00:08:38,000
don't talk nonsense.

204
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:46,840
Did Director Lin scold you?

205
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:51,559
You mean helping her up?

206
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:53,240
Why didn't you catch Zhang Diao'e?

207
00:08:55,519 --> 00:08:55,919
Seriously,

208
00:08:56,039 --> 00:08:57,120
if I had been there,

209
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:57,799
I definitely would have...

210
00:09:03,879 --> 00:09:04,399
Forget it.

211
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:10,240
Brother Dong.

212
00:09:15,919 --> 00:09:16,279
Everyone's here.

213
00:09:16,519 --> 00:09:17,559
Good.

214
00:09:17,559 --> 00:09:18,600
I'm treating everyone

215
00:09:18,679 --> 00:09:19,360
to something.

216
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:20,799
Order whatever you want.

217
00:09:21,159 --> 00:09:21,679
It's on me.

218
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:23,360
How generous.

219
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:24,120
Did you win the lottery?

220
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:24,799
No.

221
00:09:25,279 --> 00:09:25,639
The funding for my

222
00:09:25,759 --> 00:09:27,159
National Natural Science Foundation youth project

223
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,080
has come through.

224
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:28,679
So I'm celebrating.

225
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:30,360
What?

226
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:31,240
Say that again.

227
00:09:31,759 --> 00:09:32,399
I'm celebrating.

228
00:09:32,879 --> 00:09:33,519
The sentence before that.

229
00:09:35,159 --> 00:09:36,120
My NSFC youth grant

230
00:09:36,159 --> 00:09:36,919
has been funded.

231
00:09:37,399 --> 00:09:38,840
The NSFC?

232
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:40,120
Dr. Du,

233
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:41,919
when did this happen?

234
00:09:42,799 --> 00:09:43,879
I applied in March.

235
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:44,679
The results

236
00:09:44,799 --> 00:09:45,759
came out in August.

237
00:09:46,039 --> 00:09:46,720
Then I submitted

238
00:09:46,759 --> 00:09:47,519
the project plan.

239
00:09:47,799 --> 00:09:48,720
Today I got an email saying

240
00:09:48,759 --> 00:09:49,679
the funds had been released.

241
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:55,879
Isn't that

242
00:09:57,039 --> 00:09:57,600
the usual process?

243
00:09:59,000 --> 00:09:59,480
Yes.

244
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:02,440
Oh my God.

245
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:03,159
Dr. Du,

246
00:10:03,519 --> 00:10:04,559
you're unbelievable.

247
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,039
You graduated from a non-elite university.

248
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:07,519
I'm not saying

249
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:08,559
talented people can't come from such schools.

250
00:10:09,159 --> 00:10:11,039
But that's the NSFC.

251
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:12,759
Do you know how many senior doctors

252
00:10:12,799 --> 00:10:14,080
have obsessed over it,

253
00:10:14,240 --> 00:10:15,679
gone crazy over it,

254
00:10:15,799 --> 00:10:16,559
and practically beaten their heads against the wall?

255
00:10:16,879 --> 00:10:17,440
Just look at everyone here.

256
00:10:18,039 --> 00:10:18,840
Brother Zhan

257
00:10:18,879 --> 00:10:19,960
has failed again and again.

258
00:10:20,559 --> 00:10:21,039
And kept trying again and again.

259
00:10:21,879 --> 00:10:22,440
Brother Zhu's

260
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:23,799
reviewer comments alone

261
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:24,720
could fill a whole bookshelf.

262
00:10:25,039 --> 00:10:26,159
Brother Dong

263
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:27,519
hasn't gotten anything either.

264
00:10:27,519 --> 00:10:28,440
How did you manage

265
00:10:28,519 --> 00:10:29,399
to win one in your first year of specialty training?

266
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:30,519
And the most infuriating part

267
00:10:30,519 --> 00:10:32,080
is how casually

268
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:33,000
you say it.

269
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:34,639
Compared with operating,

270
00:10:34,679 --> 00:10:35,840
it really is easier.

271
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:37,759
That's arrogant.

272
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:39,720
We have to make him pay.

273
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:40,519
Absolutely.

274
00:10:40,559 --> 00:10:42,039
Make him pay. Make him pay.

275
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:43,039
Write down whatever

276
00:10:43,159 --> 00:10:44,039
you want to eat.

277
00:10:44,159 --> 00:10:45,080
Write it down.

278
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:45,919
Go on, write.

279
00:10:45,919 --> 00:10:46,799
King crab.

280
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:47,519
Order it.

281
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:48,799
Pick something expensive.

282
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:49,279
Something expensive.

283
00:10:49,279 --> 00:10:50,039
What did we want last time?

284
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:50,879
King crab.

285
00:10:50,879 --> 00:10:52,399
King crab.

286
00:10:52,399 --> 00:10:53,120
King crab.

287
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:54,759
I looked it up.

288
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:56,559
Dr. Du published

289
00:10:56,559 --> 00:10:58,360
quite a few high-impact papers during his PhD.

290
00:10:58,840 --> 00:10:59,559
One of them

291
00:10:59,559 --> 00:11:01,279
had an impact factor above ten.

292
00:11:01,519 --> 00:11:03,399
So winning an NSFC youth grant

293
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:04,279
during specialty training isn't surprising.

294
00:11:05,639 --> 00:11:07,080
At least he has one talent.

295
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:08,320
If you can't hold a retractor,

296
00:11:08,679 --> 00:11:09,679
then hold a pen.

297
00:11:10,279 --> 00:11:11,679
Everyone is good

298
00:11:11,679 --> 00:11:12,480
at different things.

299
00:11:13,039 --> 00:11:14,159
