364
00:14:14,639 --> 00:14:15,519
over the past two days.

365
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,080
What she did that day

366
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:18,679
actually had a reason.

367
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:22,200
In her first year of her PhD,

368
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:23,720
she saved a six-year-old child.

369
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:25,799
The child

370
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:27,080
was somehow

371
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:28,240
hanging outside

372
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:29,759
an apartment window.

373
00:14:30,919 --> 00:14:32,120
Dr. Ye happened to pass by.

374
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:33,519
When she saw the child falling,

375
00:14:33,519 --> 00:14:34,759
she rushed over and caught her.

376
00:14:35,759 --> 00:14:36,440
The child

377
00:14:36,639 --> 00:14:37,799
only suffered minor abrasions,

378
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,919
but Dr. Ye was badly injured.

379
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:42,720
She had multiple fractures

380
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:43,559
and spent more than a month

381
00:14:43,559 --> 00:14:44,879
in the ICU.

382
00:14:46,240 --> 00:14:47,399
The child who fell

383
00:14:47,799 --> 00:14:48,919
had severe autism.

384
00:14:50,399 --> 00:14:51,360
She couldn't understand

385
00:14:53,440 --> 00:14:55,000
or express gratitude.

386
00:14:55,559 --> 00:14:56,679
But the parents

387
00:14:57,679 --> 00:14:58,919
never even visited Dr. Ye

388
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:00,120
in the hospital.

389
00:15:01,159 --> 00:15:02,519
Dr. Ye didn't dare tell her own parents,

390
00:15:03,759 --> 00:15:04,360
so she endured it alone

391
00:15:04,399 --> 00:15:05,559
in the ICU

392
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:07,000
until she was discharged.

393
00:15:07,879 --> 00:15:08,679
She only met that family

394
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:09,799
later at the police station.

395
00:15:28,279 --> 00:15:29,000
They even asked,

396
00:15:29,879 --> 00:15:31,279
"Why did you bother catching her?"

397
00:15:39,799 --> 00:15:40,960
Dr. Ye had believed

398
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:42,879
she had saved a young life,

399
00:15:44,039 --> 00:15:45,519
but instead, her help was rejected

400
00:15:46,039 --> 00:15:47,080
and she was even blamed.

401
00:15:48,679 --> 00:15:49,720
So she suffered

402
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:51,279
both physical and psychological trauma.

403
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:54,080
After that incident,

404
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:55,679
she changed completely.

405
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:58,440
Physical injuries heal more easily,

406
00:15:59,360 --> 00:16:00,519
but psychological wounds

407
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:03,159
are much harder to recover from.

408
00:16:07,399 --> 00:16:08,679
That's true.

409
00:16:10,039 --> 00:16:12,480
Please look out for her, Director Zhou.

410
00:16:13,039 --> 00:16:13,639
